  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2022-03-16",
    "date": "2022-03-21T18:55:41Z",
    "text": "Long-Term Care Affordability Act\n\nThis bill allows the use of tax-exempt retirement plan distributions to pay for long-term health care insurance. Specifically, it excludes such distributions from the gross income of an insured individual up to $2,500 for per individual in a taxable year.\n\nIt also imposes reporting requirements on plans and insured individuals and requires a description of long-term care insurance arrangements and facts sheets for employers and workers."
